#X text 1067 434, f 108;
#X text 1089 32 - IN GENERAL ITS GOOD TO HAVE AN ANTI-ALIASING FILTER WHEN RECORDING \, AROUND 20000[Hz] \; - DO I NEED TO FADE-IN/OUT IN AUDACITY BEFORE BRINGING TO PD? ----> NO NEED \, SINCE THA HANN ENVELOPE WILL DO THE TASK OF ZERO-FADING \; - THE QUESTION IS: SHOULD I DO THE ANALYSIS AND RESYNTHESIS ON ONE OR MULTI-OSCILLATOR WAVETABLE? -----> SEEMS LIKE THAT IT WILL NOT AFFECT THE AVAILABLE HARMONICS. BUT TO TEST BOTH \; - H_MAX = (NYQUIST-FREQUENCY = 24000)/(MAX f0 WANT TO PLAY) \; - EXPORT 3 DIFFERENT WAVETABLE FROM THE ORIGINAL ONE \; ---> 1) LOW NOTES (UPTO 200Hz): INT(24000/200) = 120 => UPTO 120-(20) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \; ---> 2) MIDDLE NOTES (UPTO 1000Hz) :INT(24000/1000) = 24 => UPTO 24-(4) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \; ---> 3) HIGH NOTES (UPTO 4000Hz): INT(24000/4000) = 6 => UPTO 6-(1) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \; BASICALLY 1) FIRST I SHOULD PLAY THE WAVETABLE AT UPPER THRESHOLD - 2) ANALYSIS AND RESYNTHESIS REMOVING HIGH FREQEUNCIES - 3) PUT THE RESYNTHESIZED WAVE INSIDE CORRESPONDING WAVE ARRAY - 4) EXPORT \;, f 109;
#X obj 323 266 cnv 20 240 80 empty empty empty 20 12 0 12 #e0e0e0 #404040 0;
#X text 326 270 MULTIPLE BAND-LIMITED WAVETABLE: \; - ONE FOR LOW NOTES 30-200 \; - ONE FOR MEDIUM NOTES 200-1000 \; - ONE FOR HIGH NOTES 1000-4000 \;;
#X obj 1412 510 s \$0-RECORD;
#X obj 44 563 r \$0-RECORD;
#X text 963 421 HITTING RECORD WILL PLAY THE OSCILLATOR AT CURRENTY SET FREQUENCY (UPPER THRESHOLD OF ONE OF THE BANDS) FROM PHASE 0 IT WILL PUT INTO ONE OF THE ARRAYS BASED ON WHAT IS INLETTED TO IT --- I CAN ADD ANOTHER INLET OR GUI BANG TO SAVE TO DISK WITH PROPER NAME SETTING \; NOTE: BEFORE RECORDING ONLY OSCILLATOR 0 SHOULD BE ON! \;;
#X text 112 652 TO BE REPLACED BY ANALYSIS RESYNTHESIS;
#X text 774 313 SHOULD ENVELOPE BE ON WHEN RECORDING?;
